########################################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
	"PGstandard.pl",	# Standard macros for PG language
	"MathObjects.pl",
	"PGML.pl",
	"parserPopUp.pl",
	"parserMultiAnswer.pl",
	"weightedGrader.pl",
	"source.pl",			# allows code to be displayed on certain sites
	"PGcourse.pl", 	 # Customization file for the course
);

#######################################################
#Setup

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

Context("Numeric");		# or Complex

#---------------Tolerance------------------#
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.02,
tolType=>'relative');  #relative or absolute

#-------------- Image Scaling---------------#
$imgScale =0.35;
$width = $imgScale*1361;		#aspect ratio
$height = $imgScale*1353;

#---- Random variables for this problem --------#
$mass = random(2,5,0.1);
$tension = random(1000,1200,1);
$intVel = random(1,5,0.1);
$length = random(1.5,2.5,0.01);

#---- Formulas to compute answers --------------#
$natFreq = sqrt(2*$tension/($mass*$length));
$A = $intVel/$natFreq;

#---- Answers to the problem -----------------------#
$ansA = "$A*sin($natFreq*t)";

########################################################;
#PGML

BEGIN_PGML	

[@ image( "20-R-VIB-DY-3.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

A new type of punching bag to be used in space consists of a [`m =`] [`[$mass]`] [`kg`] 
ball suspended mid air by two [`l =`] [`[$length]`] [`m`] taut ropes, each with a tension 
of [`T =`] [`[$tension]`] [`N`]. One rope connects the ball to the ceiling and the other to the ground. 
If an impact results in a initial horizontal velocity [`v_0 =`] [`[$intVel]`] [`m/s`], 
find the equation of horizontal displacement.

END_PGML

BEGIN_TEXT

 $BR\{ans_rule(25) \}

END_TEXT

ANS(function_cmp($ansA,'t'));



BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

Answers

[@ image( "20-R-VIB-DY-3.pdf", width=>[0], height=>[0] ) @]*

END_PGML_SOLUTION


ENDDOCUMENT();
